BBC History Magazine is Britain’s bestselling history magazine. It is published every four weeks and sold around the globe, in print and many digital editions.

In each issue we offer fresh perspectives on a wide range of historical topics – everything from Ancient Egypt to the Tudors, medieval life to the Second World War. Our articles are all written by expert historians, including well-known names such as Dan Snow, Antony Beevor, Mary Beard and Michael Wood. Alongside in-depth features, every edition also includes a comprehensive book reviews section, the latest history news and opinion, and ideas for heritage visits in the UK and abroad.

Throughout, the magazine is written in a knowledgeable yet accessible style and beautifully illustrated with historical images from the periods covered.

Alongside the magazine, we are also the creators of the award-winning History Extra podcast, which is available to download for free each week and features interviews with some of the biggest names in the history world
